ⲉⲣⲓ means bread. It consistently occurs in Leviticus 22:7. According to Crum, ϣⲏⲣⲓ occurs as a variant of ⲉⲣⲓ in this verse. Westendorf mentions it in Koptisches Handwörterbuch, along with its etymology. KELLIA has rightfully accepted it as such.
